According to crime-watch account @crimeairnetwork , a group of alleged farm attackers have been arrested in Lydenburg, Mpumalanga. The arrests were reportedly due to cooperation between a security company and the local community. One firearm was reportedly seized after one alleged perpetrator was shot. Stolen goods were also reportedly recovered. 13 FARM ATTACKERS NAILED IN LYDENBURG. MP. SECURITY CO. &amp; COMMUNITY GOT THEM. FIREARM SEIZED. 1 PERP SHOT. GOODS TAKEN RECOVERED pic.twitter.com/zlCXENBDQM &mdash; REZA (@crimeairnetwork) November 20, 2016